scene.message:
Nanjo: A megalithic ruin...{nl}
A precious piece of{nl}
cultural heritage.{waitkey}{nl}
Who built it, and for what?{nl}
It never ceases to{nl}
fascinate me.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Our principal seems{nl}
like a nice lady, but...{nl}
she's kinda girly, y'know?{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: I've got work today...{nl}
Let's just get to the{nl}
hospital and get it done.{waitkey}{ret}

Principal Oishi: My, {ctl0f:1},{nl}
out for a stroll too, dear?{nl}
Every day I ask this{waitkey}{nl}
guardian deity to watch{nl}
over our students so they{nl}
grow up well.{waitkey}{nl}
It's been my habit{nl}
since I was young.{waitkey}{ret}

{color:3}Principal Oishi.{nl}
Headmistress of St. Hermelin.{nl}
A woman who loves children{nl}
and flowers alike.{color:0}{waitkey}{ret}

Student: The principal is{nl}
such a kind person.{waitkey}{nl}
And she just loves flowers —{nl}
tends to them like they're{nl}
her own children.{waitkey}{ret}

Student: It's so loud out{nl}
there, yet it's quiet here...{waitkey}{nl}
Why aren't there any{nl}
demons around here?{nl}
God's protection, maybe?{waitkey}{ret}

Hiremon Stone{nl}
Unearthed during the school's{nl}
construction in 1963.{waitkey}{clearbox}The rock type is samaite,{nl}
though magnetic anomalies{nl}
have been detected.{waitkey}{clearbox}Legend holds that a celestial{nl}
being named Hiremon{waitkey}{nl}
cast it down from the heavens{nl}
as a guardian stone{nl}
for Mikage-cho.{waitkey}{ret}
